20/06/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Construction of the major regional oil pipeline connecting Bourgas and Alexandroupolis will create 2,300 new jobs in Bulgaria and Greece, according to Greek Deputy Development Minister George Salagoudis. 
He spoke Saturday (18 June) at the 8th international conference of the Balkan Political Club, dedicated this year to issues related to regional infrastructure. 
He added that the project -- involving Bulgaria, Greece and Russia -- would also contribute to regional stability. 
(ANA, BNR - 18/06/05)
